<chapter xml:id="ch-II-2-Probability" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Probability</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>Chapter 2 introduces students to the basics of probability. 
        The emphasis is on problems that occur naturally, both in the playing of 
        games and in natural phenomena. The binomial model is stressed, as many 
        problems arise from a sequence of either/or choices. The <xref ref="sec-2-7-Bell_Curve" text="title"/> is
         of fundamental importance in statistics and is addressed here.</p>
  </introduction>

